    "slug": "what-is-an-ai-employee",
    "raw": "---\ntitle: \"What is an AI employee?\"\ndescription: \"An AI employee is a persistent autonomous agent with its own computer — not a chatbot. Learn how Construct executes work end-to-end across email, Slack, and your apps.\"\ndate: \"2026-07-02\"\nauthor: \"Construct Team\"\ntags: [\"ai-agent\", \"product\", \"ai-employee\"]\ndraft: false\n---\n\nMost \"AI assistants\" live in a chat window. You ask a question, get an answer, and copy the result somewhere else. An **AI employee** is different: it has its own cloud computer, remembers context across sessions, and finishes multi-step work while you are away.\n\n## Chat assistant vs AI employee\n\n| | Chat assistant | AI employee (Construct) |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Interface** | Thread of messages | Virtual desktop you can watch |\n| **Work style** | Suggests what to do | Executes browser, terminal, and apps |\n| **Memory** | Session-bound | Persistent sandbox, files, and memory |\n| **Output** | Text in chat | Sent email, updated tickets, saved reports |\n\n## What Construct does day to day\n\nConstruct logs into a full virtual desktop with a browser, terminal, calendar, task tracker, and audit log. You assign outcomes:\n\n- Research a market and email a PDF report\n- Triage inbox and draft replies for approval\n- Update Linear issues from Slack messages\n- Run a recurring Monday morning competitor scan\n\nThe agent plans the steps, uses connected apps (Gmail, Notion, GitHub, and 1,000+ more), and leaves proof in your workspace and audit log.\n\n## When an AI employee makes sense\n\nChoose an AI employee when you need **recurring autonomous work**, **cross-app workflows**, or **proof of execution**. Stick with chat assistants for quick drafting and brainstorming.\n\nWant a deeper comparison? Read [Construct vs ChatGPT](/vs/chatgpt) or [all comparisons](/vs).\n"
